vPatterns promise to boost productivity and enhance the expertise of their users. Have they delivered? Is this expectation even reasonable? What should the goal of patterns be? vWhat are patterns? Many believe that patterns should capture only proven solutions, but are patterns anything more than old ideas in new packages? vPatterns owe much of their popularity toDesign Patterns−the so−called "Gang of Four" book. What service−or disservice−has this book done to the software community? vWhere will patterns go from here? Where should they go?